1
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:20,880
BANGKWAI WITTHAYAKHOM'S 100-YEAR BUILDING

2
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:23,000
- Come on.
- Go on.

3
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:28,800
Hey, No.

4
00:00:28,880 --> 00:00:29,760
Don't do it.

5
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,120
Hey, No.

6
00:00:34,760 --> 00:00:36,760
<i>There is a certain kind of madman</i>

7
00:00:38,360 --> 00:00:40,520
<i>who happens to gain power.</i>

8
00:00:41,760 --> 00:00:44,320
<i>They always try to cover up</i>
<i>their own wrongdoings</i>

9
00:00:46,640 --> 00:00:49,040
<i>with other people’s scandals.</i>

10
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:51,920
<i>But…</i>

11
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,880
<i>when an elephant dies,</i>

12
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:56,360
<i>can you really cover the whole thing</i>
<i>with a lotus leaf?</i>

13
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:06,480
BANGKWAI WITTHAYAKHOM'S 100-YEAR BUILDING

14
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:07,600
{\an8}THIS AREA IS UNDER RENOVATION.

15
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,400
{\an8}IN 25 DAYS, BANGKWAI WITTHAYAKHOM'S
100-YEAR BUILDING WILL OPEN

16
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,120
{\an8}WILL THE 100-YEAR BUILDING
REALLY BE ABLE TO OPEN FOR USE?

17
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:46,880
{\an8}<i>Bangkwai Witthayakhom's 100-Year Building</i>

18
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:48,800
{\an8}<i>has officially been handed over</i>
<i>following renovations.</i>

19
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,120
{\an8}<i>But can it really be used?</i>

20
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:53,160
{\an8}<i>The load-bearing columns</i>
<i>have major cracks in them.</i>

21
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:54,800
{\an8}<i>The cement is below spec.</i>

22
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:56,480
{\an8}<i>The steel doesn't meet standards.</i>

23
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:59,120
{\an8}<i>This reeks of corruption.</i>

24
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:03,520
Did you see what the Exclamation group
exposed about the 100-Year Building?

25
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:06,920
- How much do you think they embezzled?
- The photo is obviously the headmaster.

26
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,400
She's wearing red all over.
There's only one person like that.

27
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:12,200
- They're still going to open the building?
- That's scary.

28
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,120
Who would dare use the building?

29
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,640
Something's definitely going on.

30
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:18,960
{\an8}Look at that.
Did they repair it, or just tear it down?

31
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:21,800
{\an8}Yeah, what kind of cement is that?
Why did it crack so easily?

32
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:23,960
Look at that. The steel must be fake.

33
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:26,040
What about the other buildings?

34
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,560
<i>Where are you?</i>

35
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:30,640
<i>I see Tae.</i>

36
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,520
STORAGE ROOM
NO ENTRY

37
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:37,720
Everyone, the president's going inside.

38
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:47,480
{\an8}EURO PANG

39
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:50,720
{\an8}Who called this meeting in this spot?

40
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:53,280
Why aren't we using
the rooftop of Building 6 like before?

41
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:56,080
Weren't you the one
who typed that in the group?

42
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:59,120
I'm not that out of it, Wanda.

43
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,440
{\an8}You're definitely out of it.

44
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,480
{\an8}SEE YOU TOMORROW MORNING
AT THE STORAGE ROOM UNDER BUILDING 2

45
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:12,840
Hey…

46
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:13,840
That wasn't me.

47
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,399
Are you teasing me?

48
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,800
I'll show you.

49
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,399
SEE YOU TOMORROW MORNING
AT THE STORAGE ROOM UNDER BUILDING 2

50
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,680
Look. It wasn't me.

51
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:26,880
You're joking, right?

52
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,520
Beng, was it you?

53
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:29,680
Not me.

54
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:32,600
- Shit.
- What?

55
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:34,920
Someone else is in our chat room. Look.

56
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:37,440
Oops. I got caught.

57
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:38,360
Hey.

58
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:39,400
<i>Whose voice was that?</i>

59
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:56,520
Hi.

60
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,400
I'm Nanno.

61
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:00,040
I'm a new student here.

62
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,960
Mind if I join the party?

63
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:10,400
Who sent you? The headmaster?

64
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:12,520
No.

65
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,680
I came to help you, Pankham.

66
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:16,760
Oh? You two know each other?

67
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:18,600
I know the whole team.

68
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,760
Hey, guys, what's going on in there?

69
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:23,720
Shit.

70
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:26,120
The Boy Scouts are here.

71
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:33,920
Shit, do you have anything
you haven't told us?

72
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:34,840
I don't know her.

73
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,840
What are you doing here?

74
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:41,920
Where I sit is none of your business.

75
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,720
Do you see this badge?

76
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:48,760
I received orders directly
from the headmaster

77
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:52,000
to monitor those who undermine
and sabotage the school.

78
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,080
And I have a feeling

79
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:58,560
I can smell the rotten
Bangkwai Exclamation group around here.

80
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:00,520
Can you smell it too?

81
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,200
Other than your bad breath,

82
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:04,080
I don't smell shit.

83
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:11,400
‪NO ENTRY

84
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:15,600
‪Shit.

85
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:17,280
I think we're busted.

86
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:40,640
Hey. It's coming
from the front of the school.

87
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:52,200
Shit.

88
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:54,320
- Hurry.
- Damn it.

89
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:57,040
- Slowly.
- Sit there.

90
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:58,920
Be quiet.

91
00:06:59,000 --> 00:06:59,840
No, no.

92
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,200
- Let go first.
- Alright.

93
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:03,280
Who's this?

94
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:06,160
Hi, Tae. I'm Nanno.

95
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,200
Nanno who?

96
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:11,360
Your gang is amazing.

97
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:14,560
The Exclamation gang.

98
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:24,400
You want to expose the corruption
in the building's renovation, right?

99
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:28,560
I have a plan. I'll help.

100
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:41,600
BANGKWAI WITTHAYAKHOM

101
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:43,320
What happened?

102
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:49,160
- Shit.
- Shit.

103
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:51,160
Teacher, now the school's name is Bang…

104
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:53,040
{\an8}BANGKHUAY WITTHAYAKHOM'S 100-YEAR BUILDING

105
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,960
Students, go to your classrooms!

106
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:57,960
Now. Go.

107
00:07:58,040 --> 00:07:59,680
You too. Run!

108
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:04,440
How obscene.

109
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:10,360
{\an8}#CORRUPTRENOVATIONWILLKILLUSALL

110
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:12,040
{\an8}<i>Instead of fixing their wrongdoings…</i>

111
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,600
{\an8}IN 24 DAYS, BANGKWAI WITTHAYAKHOM'S
100-YEAR BUILDING WILL OPEN

112
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,920
<i>…evil people choose to cover it up</i>
<i>with something else</i>

113
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:19,800
<i>to make others obedient</i>

114
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:22,440
<i>and easier to control.</i>

115
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,280
How cute.

116
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:27,040
HEADMASTER YAEM THATSARAI

117
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,120
This morning,

118
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:31,280
what were the students screaming about?

119
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:32,640
Nothing, Headmaster.

120
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:35,240
They were just screaming
about a shipped couple they follow.

121
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:17,000
Mr. Dobby, do you also feel

122
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:21,520
that these people
are hiding something from us?

123
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,520
Come in.

124
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,520
Well, hello.

125
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,600
The students are shocked by the news

126
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:49,800
from this secret page, Headmaster.

127
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,000
Look, Mr. Dobby.

128
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:54,960
Are you scared?

129
00:09:55,040 --> 00:09:57,520
Why don't you go run around for a bit?

130
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:59,360
Go take a walk.

131
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,440
Thank you.

132
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:04,080
Thank you very much.

133
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:09,920
This new student sent me an email

134
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:12,920
about the Exclamation group.

135
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,680
They're just an underground page.

136
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:17,880
They make things up
without having any real facts.

137
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,880
But the news is already out.

138
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:22,880
And the students already believe it.

139
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:26,720
Deputy Headmasters, perhaps you're too old

140
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:29,120
to keep up with the students anymore.

141
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:32,160
Maybe it's time
to let the new student handle it instead.

142
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,560
Just a moment.

143
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:51,600
Beautiful.

144
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:52,760
Thank you.

145
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:56,240
Don't disappoint Mr. Dobby and me.

146
00:10:57,520 --> 00:10:58,520
Yes.

147
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:13,840
Wait, Nanno.

148
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:18,720
From now on, don't do that again, okay?

149
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:21,560
What do you mean?

150
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:24,000
How do I say this?

151
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:25,000
Normally,

152
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:28,160
we teachers are the headmaster's advisors.

153
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,240
HAVING A JOB AND A SALARY ISN'T
AS IMPORTANT AS HAVING GOOD COWORKERS

154
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:33,320
But suddenly,
you reported directly to the headmaster

155
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,840
- like we are--
- Just useless ornaments?

156
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:38,240
Yes, ornaments.

157
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:40,120
Hey, you.

158
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,280
I'll…

159
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:43,520
- Take her away first.
- You.

160
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:48,400
Nanno.

161
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:51,320
I know you're a smart student.

162
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:53,800
Having you help keep an eye on things

163
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,040
makes me very happy.

164
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:57,880
But from now on,

165
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:00,760
if you find anything,
could you tell me first?

166
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:03,880
Hmm.

167
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:08,200
So, Deputy Headmaster Kai, you also don't
like students going over your head, right?

168
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:13,440
I understand.

169
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:16,840
So now I'm curious.

170
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:19,720
What will you do about the news
that the Exclamation group released?

171
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:32,080
DEPUTY KAI, DEPUTY NOO,
DEPUTY NOK, DEPUTY TAO

172
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:34,600
{\an8}NANNO

173
00:12:34,680 --> 00:12:37,240
<i>The famous Bangkwai school shipped couple</i>

174
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:40,360
<i>secretly unfollowed each other.</i>
<i>Is their relationship about to end?</i>

175
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,840
They said a shipped couple
is about to break up.

176
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:45,400
- Is it the same one?
- Yeah, the same one.

177
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:46,200
WHY ARE THEY BREAKING UP?

178
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:47,760
Such a shame about this couple.

179
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:54,040
BB and Taetae are breaking up?

180
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:55,400
Are they really breaking up?

181
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:56,680
They were so cute together.

182
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:57,640
- THEY'LL MAKE UP SOON
- GIVE IT THREE DAYS

183
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,520
- They really are breaking up.
- What a pity.

184
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,960
Didn't you say you wanted to join us?

185
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:15,840
I already told you.

186
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,760
I have a plan.

187
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:19,600
Here it is.

188
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:22,680
I've become
the headmaster's special advisor.

189
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:28,040
Has any Exclamation member
ever gotten access like this?

190
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,160
Keep your eyes on the flagpole.

191
00:13:49,960 --> 00:13:51,880
IN 23 DAYS, BANGKWAI WITTHAYAKHOM'S
100-YEAR BUILDING WILL OPEN

192
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:24,560
Hey.

193
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:26,640
Students, move aside.

194
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:28,320
- Move aside.
- Go.

195
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,240
{\an8}EVEN THE FLAGPOLE DIDN'T SURVIVE

196
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:35,240
{\an8}#CORRUPTRENOVATIONWILLKILLUSALL

197
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:37,280
Corruption was even involved
in the building of the flagpole?

198
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:40,000
Damn, then how bad
must the 100-Year Building be?

199
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,240
That's scary.

200
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:44,640
Yeah. Why hasn't anyone
spoken out about it?

201
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:47,280
They say the headmaster
is the one behind the corruption.

202
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:48,640
Really?

203
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:52,280
The Exclamation group is amazing,
exposing the truth for our school.

204
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:55,080
Yeah. If it weren't for them,
we wouldn't even know.

205
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:05,720
I bet the headmaster and her deputies
can't sit still right now.

206
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:06,920
I bet everything will go quiet again soon.

207
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:10,520
- They're awesome. Who are they anyway?
- Yeah, I want to join them.

208
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:12,160
Yeah, so we can expose this corruption.

209
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,840
Do you think
the Exclamation group will get taken down?

210
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:23,640
Come in.

211
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:35,520
How did the Exclamation group
get this information?

212
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:40,360
The rigged bidding and locked specs
for the flagpole, right?

213
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:44,160
The contractor was Ruja Construction,

214
00:15:44,760 --> 00:15:48,200
the same company that handled
the renovation of our 100-Year Building.

215
00:15:49,040 --> 00:15:50,760
What a coincidence.

216
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:57,640
Not a coincidence.

217
00:15:58,160 --> 00:15:59,120
I approved it myself.

218
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:02,040
That company does good work.
It's reliable.

219
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,760
We've used them for years.

220
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:10,280
And it just so happens

221
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:13,200
that Mrs. Ruja, the company's owner,

222
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:15,920
is your wife.

223
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:22,000
Well, the 100-Year Building
is exactly what its name says.

224
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:24,000
The structure
has been around for a long time.

225
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,920
How could I let
an unfamiliar company handle it?

226
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,800
Of course I had to choose
a company I trust.

227
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:32,640
Trusting your wife is a good thing.

228
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:41,840
I won't keep beating around the bush.

229
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,080
I'm the one responsible for this project.

230
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:46,600
And I've already signed off
on its completion.

231
00:16:47,920 --> 00:16:50,240
- If the building can't open on schedule,
- If the building can't open on schedule,

232
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:51,760
- I'll be in serious trouble.
- you'll be in serious trouble.

233
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:53,000
Checkmate.

234
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:02,160
I understand.

235
00:17:05,319 --> 00:17:09,119
Could you recommend
a feng shui master for me urgently?

236
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:13,400
BANGKHUAY WITTHAYAKHOM'S 100-YEAR BUILDING

237
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:16,000
{\an8}IN 20 DAYS, BANGKWAI WITTHAYAKHOM'S
100-YEAR BUILDING WILL OPEN

238
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:22,440
NO ENTRY

239
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:27,960
Hey, guys, check out this live stream.

240
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:29,920
What live stream?

241
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,280
BANGKWAI WITTHAYAKHOM SCHOOL

242
00:17:32,360 --> 00:17:34,000
<i>Damn.</i>

243
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:36,240
<i>What the hell is this?</i>

244
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:38,440
<i>This is the real reason.</i>

245
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:40,880
Underneath here are inauspicious things.

246
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:42,640
- <i>Someone did this.</i>
- Look at this.

247
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:44,480
<i>That means they have ill intentions</i>

248
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:46,320
<i>and malicious motives.</i>

249
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:50,520
<i>And this is their symbol.</i>

250
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:52,880
Shit.

251
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,040
- Shit.
- What the hell?

252
00:17:55,760 --> 00:17:57,160
<i>Hey, that's an exclamation mark.</i>

253
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:01,920
- Let's leave first. Go.
- Yeah.

254
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:03,640
‪-Nobel.
‪-No, come on.

255
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:05,280
Slowly, carefully.

256
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:06,200
Come on.

257
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:09,960
Get up.

258
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:10,880
What's wrong?

259
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:11,960
Nanno.

260
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:13,480
Nanno is one of us.

261
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:16,720
Nanno brought the Boy Scouts this way.
What do you mean one of us?

262
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:23,000
Hey, we have to run first.

263
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:24,480
All our group data is in here.

264
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:25,800
Shit.

265
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:30,040
Hey, this way, guys.

266
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:31,640
Hurry up.

267
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:32,760
Go.

268
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:41,240
- You guys can go.
- Exclamation group! Open the door.

269
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:44,240
- I know you're inside.
- We'll handle it.

270
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:46,040
- Open the door.
- Go, Beng, go.

271
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:49,760
- Hold on tight.
- If you don't open it, I'll break it down.

272
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:51,960
- I warned you. Open it.
- Careful.

273
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:58,680
Break it down.

274
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,280
Students,

275
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:21,080
these two are members
of the Exclamation group,

276
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:25,920
the group that spreads false accusations
about our school without any evidence.

277
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:30,720
Their claim that
the 100-Year Building will collapse

278
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:32,800
is completely false.

279
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:37,160
And I'm not speaking without proof.

280
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:40,840
I have invited someone
with authority on the matter

281
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:42,640
to speak to all of you.

282
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:44,600
Please welcome him.

283
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:46,440
<i>Hello.</i>

284
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:49,240
<i>I am the engineer</i>
<i>responsible for the 100-Year Building.</i>

285
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:52,360
<i>I assure all students</i>

286
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:54,040
<i>that the 100-Year Building</i>

287
00:19:54,120 --> 00:19:57,640
<i>has been renovated properly, according</i>
<i>to all civil engineering standards.</i>

288
00:19:58,160 --> 00:19:59,480
<i>You can rest easy.</i>

289
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,000
<i>All the rumors circulating in this school</i>

290
00:20:02,520 --> 00:20:03,840
<i>are fake news.</i>

291
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:10,160
So, if you don't believe an engineer,

292
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:12,040
who will you believe?

293
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:13,720
Exactly.

294
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:18,920
Therefore, what these two did
deserves expulsion.

295
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,280
Shit.

296
00:20:22,080 --> 00:20:22,920
Expel them.

297
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,440
- Yeah, expel them.
- Expel?

298
00:20:25,480 --> 00:20:26,480
But…

299
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:28,880
I'm a kind person.

300
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:31,320
I can't just expel them like that.

301
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:34,240
So I'd like to give them one more chance.

302
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:37,080
Potae, open it.

303
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:44,560
This is the face of the Exclamation group

304
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:49,080
that spreads fake news
to destroy our school.

305
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:51,320
Now you've all seen

306
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:54,040
how many of them there are, right?

307
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:56,360
One.

308
00:20:57,080 --> 00:20:58,240
Two.

309
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:00,240
Three.

310
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:01,600
Four.

311
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:03,360
And five.

312
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:06,120
The other three members

313
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,800
are standing here right now, right?

314
00:21:09,320 --> 00:21:12,800
If either of you can tell me

315
00:21:13,320 --> 00:21:14,840
who the other three are,

316
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:17,720
I will regard you as witnesses.

317
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:20,480
That means
you won't receive any punishment.

318
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:25,200
No, remember our ideals. Don't do it.

319
00:21:28,760 --> 00:21:31,320
You don't need to say their names.

320
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:33,640
Just point at them.

321
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:44,000
No, don't do it.

322
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:45,040
Just point.

323
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:46,760
- Remember our ideals.
- Come on.

324
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,560
Point.

325
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:54,200
Tell us.

326
00:21:56,960 --> 00:21:57,800
Hey, No.

327
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,200
Point.

328
00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:10,560
Hey, No!

329
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:12,120
Don't do it.

330
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:16,000
Point at them.

331
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:17,040
Point at them.

332
00:22:19,760 --> 00:22:20,960
Hey?

333
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:22,120
- Potae?
- Potae?

334
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:24,520
- Really?
- Really?

335
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:26,280
- Damn you.
- You? What the hell?

336
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:31,120
Down with the corrupt!

337
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:33,040
Long live Exclamation!

338
00:22:33,640 --> 00:22:35,000
Do it for me.

339
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:36,640
Destroy them.

340
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:38,040
Ugh!

341
00:22:38,560 --> 00:22:41,680
These two are hereby expelled
from Bangkwai School immediately.

342
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:42,760
Take them away.

343
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:44,840
Get out. Get out.

344
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:46,640
- Get out.
- Damn, No. I love you.

345
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:49,720
Get out. Get out.

346
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:54,560
Get out.

347
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:56,560
IN 20 DAYS

348
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:58,560
IN 19 DAYS

349
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:06,480
NO ENTRY

350
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:21,480
5:30 P.M. - THIRD FLOOR COMPUTER ROOM

351
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:22,440
What do we do now?

352
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:25,720
We have to do it for Nobel and Tae.

353
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:29,400
We have to stop
the 100-Year Building from opening.

354
00:23:30,120 --> 00:23:32,360
But our futures matter too.

355
00:23:32,440 --> 00:23:34,120
If I get expelled now,

356
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:35,920
my dad will kill me.

357
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:39,600
But if the 100-Year Building collapses,
we'll be dead too.

358
00:23:40,240 --> 00:23:41,240
And in that case…

359
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:42,960
we'd be dead for real.

360
00:23:46,120 --> 00:23:48,960
The engineer already confirmed

361
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:51,280
that the building won't collapse.

362
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:53,360
You actually believe that headmaster?

363
00:23:54,760 --> 00:23:57,200
You saw the condition yourself.
Did you forget already?

364
00:23:57,280 --> 00:23:59,080
But we're not engineers.

365
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:02,040
Even if it really collapsed,

366
00:24:02,120 --> 00:24:03,840
no one would care anyway.

367
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:08,960
Why should we gamble our futures for this?

368
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,280
It's okay, Beng.

369
00:24:15,080 --> 00:24:17,720
If you're not comfortable with this
or if you want to quit…

370
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:21,800
I understand.

371
00:24:31,360 --> 00:24:38,040
BANGKWAI WITTHAYAKHOM'S 100-YEAR BUILDING

372
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:46,240
<i>Even if it really did collapse,</i>

373
00:24:46,320 --> 00:24:48,320
<i>no one would care anyway.</i>

374
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:55,160
NO ENTRY

375
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:07,360
5:30 P.M. - THIRD FLOOR COMPUTER ROOM

376
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:13,040
5:39 P.M.

377
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:32,160
Sorry. I ran into some Scouts,
so I had to take a detour.

378
00:25:34,680 --> 00:25:35,880
I thought you weren't coming.

379
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:39,080
Shall we start?

380
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:40,640
Sure.

381
00:25:45,960 --> 00:25:47,000
What was that sound?

382
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:11,040
Ugh, not her again.

383
00:26:11,120 --> 00:26:12,720
Did you bring Nanno here too?

384
00:26:14,160 --> 00:26:16,640
I didn't bring her. I came alone.

385
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:19,640
You're telling me
you came in and didn't see her?

386
00:26:20,160 --> 00:26:21,200
Listen to me first, Wanda.

387
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:23,160
Pankham, I can't stand you anymore.

388
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:25,320
I can't believe you brought Nanno here.

389
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:29,680
Nanno, how long have you been there?

390
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:31,880
And how did you know we were meeting here?

391
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:33,880
What's wrong with you, Pankham?

392
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:36,520
You're still talking to her?

393
00:26:37,160 --> 00:26:39,720
She already got
two of our friends expelled.

394
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:42,600
Wait, Wanda.

395
00:26:42,680 --> 00:26:44,720
I have something to show you.

396
00:26:55,120 --> 00:26:56,280
How did you get this?

397
00:26:57,960 --> 00:26:59,680
I was hiding in that room.

398
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:02,200
Just like I was hiding in this one.

399
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:06,680
You didn't even know I was here.

400
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:11,920
I'll send it to you.

401
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:21,200
If the Exclamation group
releases this clip,

402
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:23,840
they're finished.

403
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:40,000
{\an8}<i>The engineer who spoke earlier was fake.</i>

404
00:27:40,080 --> 00:27:42,880
{\an8}<i>It was actually Potae</i>
<i>from the Scout group,</i>

405
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:45,440
{\an8}<i>deepfaking someone's face.</i>

406
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:48,240
{\an8}- <i>And the person behind it is…</i>
- <i>I am the engineer.</i>

407
00:27:48,320 --> 00:27:49,880
{\an8}<i>I assure all students…</i>

408
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:53,120
{\an8}<i>If they keep insisting</i>
<i>on opening the building,</i>

409
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:54,720
{\an8}<i>it will collapse for sure.</i>

410
00:27:54,800 --> 00:27:56,560
{\an8}#CORRUPTRENOVATIONWILLKILLUSALL

411
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:58,640
IN 17 DAYS

412
00:27:58,720 --> 00:28:00,560
Guys, come look at this.

413
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:02,480
The engineer was fake.

414
00:28:04,600 --> 00:28:05,520
I told you.

415
00:28:07,960 --> 00:28:09,320
Shit.

416
00:28:17,080 --> 00:28:18,920
Deputy Kai is corrupt.

417
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:20,480
They even used AI to fake an engineer?

418
00:28:20,560 --> 00:28:22,880
- Then the headmaster is corrupt too?
- One hundred percent.

419
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:32,400
IN 16 DAYS

420
00:28:32,480 --> 00:28:34,360
That Exclamation group
still hasn't given up.

421
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:36,880
Our students aren't even
paying attention to this anymore.

422
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,440
But the pillar is right there.

423
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,680
And the repair budget is already used up.

424
00:28:52,760 --> 00:28:54,360
I don't want the headmaster to find out.

425
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:00,080
Maybe the sacred spirits can help.

426
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:06,720
HAVING A JOB AND A SALARY ISN'T
AS IMPORTANT AS HAVING GOOD COWORKERS

427
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:10,840
<i>Taetae and BB broke up</i>
<i>because of a third person.</i>

428
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:11,880
Hey, who is it?

429
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:13,720
Did someone really cause them to breakup?

430
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:22,440
<i>BB blocked Taetae. Or maybe someone</i>
<i>used black magic on them.</i>

431
00:29:22,520 --> 00:29:23,360
Do they really have to do this?

432
00:29:23,440 --> 00:29:25,960
How can we help them?

433
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:34,480
<i>The Sacred 100-Year Pillar</i>
<i>grants every wish.</i>

434
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:40,640
<i>Twisting the truth and diverting attention</i>

435
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:45,760
<i>are the art of those who control the game.</i>

436
00:29:51,080 --> 00:29:52,160
What are you doing?

437
00:29:52,240 --> 00:29:55,320
The school said this pillar is sacred.
Don't you know?

438
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:56,800
Everyone in this school knows that.

439
00:30:02,040 --> 00:30:04,720
<i>Nanno, whose side are you actually on?</i>

440
00:30:10,160 --> 00:30:13,640
IN 5 DAYS

441
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:35,680
Take it.

442
00:30:45,960 --> 00:30:47,560
Maybe this is all we can do.

443
00:30:53,640 --> 00:30:55,000
Honestly, I've been thinking.

444
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:57,280
What are we even doing all this for?

445
00:30:57,360 --> 00:30:59,280
No one cares.

446
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:04,960
But I want us to be wrong now.

447
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:09,640
Maybe that building
is actually strong enough.

448
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:13,240
Maybe we're just being paranoid.

449
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:21,520
IN 1 DAY

450
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:33,480
Today is a special day as we finally
reopen our 100-Year school building

451
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:35,520
after a long renovation.

452
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:38,520
The headmaster will now cut the ribbon
to officially open the building.

453
00:31:39,120 --> 00:31:41,960
Students, please follow the arranged lines

454
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:43,600
and walk into the building in order.

455
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:46,000
Your homeroom teachers will lead the way.

456
00:31:46,080 --> 00:31:47,640
Headmaster, please cut the ribbon.

457
00:31:47,720 --> 00:31:49,200
Ready?

458
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:06,320
- Headmaster, this way, please.
- Alright.

459
00:32:06,400 --> 00:32:07,640
Mr. Dobby, let's go.

460
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:11,040
All the materials used were brand new.

461
00:32:11,120 --> 00:32:14,000
Students, please line up
before entering the building.

462
00:32:14,080 --> 00:32:16,360
There are signs inside.

463
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:18,080
Go directly to your classrooms.

464
00:32:18,160 --> 00:32:19,600
First row, you may proceed.

465
00:32:40,480 --> 00:32:42,560
<i>What are we even doing all this for?</i>

466
00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:44,720
<i>No one cares.</i>

467
00:32:46,040 --> 00:32:47,920
<i>Even if it really did collapse,</i>

468
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:49,840
<i>no one would care anyway.</i>

469
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:56,320
<i>The famous couple has broken up.</i>

470
00:32:58,120 --> 00:32:59,560
<i>Twisting the truth</i>

471
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:02,080
<i>and diverting attention</i>

472
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:05,960
<i>are the art of those who control the game.</i>

473
00:33:10,720 --> 00:33:12,600
Now, Pankham.

474
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:32,280
BB, come with me.

475
00:33:32,360 --> 00:33:33,320
- What?
- Hurry.

476
00:33:39,120 --> 00:33:41,040
Are you excited? Hmm?

477
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:44,080
Alright.

478
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:45,920
I was thinking of putting
a photo here, Headmaster.

479
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:48,040
Oh, what photo?

480
00:33:48,120 --> 00:33:50,040
Let's discuss it in your new office.

481
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:52,160
- Sure.
- Please go upstairs.

482
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:54,920
The photo would lead people
to your office.

483
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:55,920
Oh, alright.

484
00:33:57,560 --> 00:33:58,760
BB, hurry.

485
00:33:59,280 --> 00:34:00,600
What the hell?

486
00:34:03,280 --> 00:34:04,840
Why did you block Taetae?

487
00:34:04,920 --> 00:34:06,360
And why did you delete
the photos from Instagram?

488
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:07,600
It's none of your business.

489
00:34:11,600 --> 00:34:13,280
Your office is on the top floor.

490
00:34:13,360 --> 00:34:15,000
The view from up there is great.

491
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:18,639
What did Taetae do to make you angry?
Tell me.

492
00:34:18,719 --> 00:34:21,480
Oh, did Taetae send you?

493
00:34:21,560 --> 00:34:22,800
Hey, answer my question.

494
00:34:22,880 --> 00:34:23,920
What did he do to make you mad?

495
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:25,040
- Just say it.
- Are you crazy?

496
00:34:25,120 --> 00:34:26,600
Hey! What are you doing?

497
00:34:34,639 --> 00:34:35,639
BB.

498
00:34:36,159 --> 00:34:37,280
I'm sorry.

499
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:40,320
Can we get back together?

500
00:34:43,320 --> 00:34:44,199
Hey.

501
00:34:44,280 --> 00:34:46,239
BB and Taetae.

502
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:47,159
Let's go.

503
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:53,679
It's so beautiful.

504
00:34:59,320 --> 00:35:00,520
Why do I feel dizzy?

505
00:35:00,600 --> 00:35:02,800
Maybe it's because the pressure
in my ears is uneven.

506
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:22,560
Don't do this.

507
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:24,440
The whole school is watching us.

508
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:55,000
Mr. Dobby.

509
00:36:19,720 --> 00:36:21,240
Deputy Kai,

510
00:36:21,320 --> 00:36:23,800
is this building really safe?

511
00:36:25,840 --> 00:36:27,000
Yes, it is.

512
00:36:46,520 --> 00:36:48,680
Everyone, go! Hurry!

513
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:51,440
Everyone, run! Hurry!

514
00:36:51,520 --> 00:36:52,440
Run!

515
00:36:52,520 --> 00:36:55,720
Everyone, run! Move.

516
00:37:19,040 --> 00:37:20,040
Here.

517
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:31,640
The 100-Year Building…

518
00:37:39,040 --> 00:37:43,520
It has now become a monument
to the Exclamation group.

519
00:37:58,760 --> 00:38:01,000
Have you thanked me yet?

520
00:38:01,640 --> 00:38:04,200
I should thank you too, Pankham,

521
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:06,080
for your cooperation.

522
00:39:06,640 --> 00:39:08,480
WHAT ARE YOU DOING, NANNO?
THE SKY IS NICE TODAY.

523
00:39:08,560 --> 00:39:10,280
HELLO, SKY. THE SKY IS NICE TODAY.

524
00:39:36,720 --> 00:39:38,120
Because the school's interests

525
00:39:38,200 --> 00:39:40,480
must be the same
as the students' interests.

526
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:42,320
Hello.

527
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:43,840
I'm Nanno. My number is two.

528
00:39:43,920 --> 00:39:47,760
My policy is "One Idea, One Kiss."

529
00:39:48,880 --> 00:39:51,040
- Nanno. Nanno.
- <i>We found evidence of fraud</i>

530
00:39:51,120 --> 00:39:53,480
<i>in the student council election.</i>

531
00:39:53,560 --> 00:39:56,640
<i>Humans tend to repeat the same mistakes</i>
<i>over and over again.</i>

532
00:39:56,720 --> 00:39:58,680
What makes you think
you're better than everyone else?

533
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:01,600
CONGRATULATIONS, MR. PARADON TANGNAITHAM,
66TH STUDENT COUNCIL PRESIDENT

534
00:41:57,840 --> 00:42:01,840
